  "root_text": {
    "an10.25:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10.25 ",
    "an10.25:0.2": "3. Mahāvagga ",
    "an10.25:0.3": "Kasiṇasutta ",
    "an10.25:1.1": "“Dasayimāni, bhikkhave, kasiṇāyatanāni. ",
    "an10.25:1.2": "Katamāni dasa? ",
    "an10.25:1.3": "Pathavīkasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṁ adho tiriyaṁ advayaṁ appamāṇaṁ; ",
    "an10.25:1.4": "āpokasiṇameko sañjānāti …pe… ",
    "an10.25:1.5": "tejokasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.6": "vāyokasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.7": "nīlakasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.8": "pītakasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.9": "lohitakasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.10": "odātakasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.11": "ākāsakasiṇameko sañjānāti … ",
    "an10.25:1.12": "viññāṇakasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṁ adho tiriyaṁ advayaṁ appamāṇaṁ. ",
    "an10.25:1.13": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dasa kasiṇāyatanānī”ti. ",
    "an10.25:1.14": "Pañcamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an10.25:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 10.25 ",
    "an10.25:0.2": "3. The Great Chapter ",
    "an10.25:0.3": "Meditation on Universals ",
    "an10.25:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these ten universal dimensions of meditation. ",
    "an10.25:1.2": "What ten? ",
    "an10.25:1.3": "Someone perceives the meditation on universal earth above, below, across, undivided and limitless. ",
    "an10.25:1.4": "They perceive the meditation on universal water … ",
    "an10.25:1.5": "the meditation on universal fire … ",
    "an10.25:1.6": "the meditation on universal air … ",
    "an10.25:1.7": "the meditation on universal blue … ",
    "an10.25:1.8": "the meditation on universal yellow … ",
    "an10.25:1.9": "the meditation on universal red … ",
    "an10.25:1.10": "the meditation on universal white … ",
    "an10.25:1.11": "the meditation on universal space … ",
    "an10.25:1.12": "They perceive the meditation on universal consciousness above, below, across, undivided and limitless. ",
    "an10.25:1.13": "These are the ten universal dimensions of meditation.” "
  },
